  <title>Cogl.Primitive.new_with_attributes</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function new_with_attributes(mode: <link xref="Cogl.VerticesMode">Cogl.VerticesMode</link>, n_vertices: Number(gint), attributes: <link xref="Cogl.Attribute">Cogl.Attribute</link>, n_attributes: Number(gint)): <link xref="Cogl.Primitive">Cogl.Primitive</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_primitive_new_with_attributes()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Combines a set of <link xref="Cogl.Attribute"/>&lt;!-- --&gt;s with a specific draw <code>mode</code>
and defines a vertex count so a <link xref="Cogl.Primitive"/> object can be retained and
drawn later with no addition information required.</p>  <p>The value passed as <code>n_vertices</code> will simply update the
<link xref="Cogl.Primitive"/> &lt;structfield&gt;n_vertices&lt;/structfield&gt; property as if
<link xref="Cogl.Primitive.set_n_vertices"/> were called. This property defines
the number of vertices to read when drawing.</p>
  <p>Since 1.6</p>
